oku puzzle instantly, but also explains the techniques and logic behind eac=
h step and how the digit to be filled in each empty cell is determined. Bec=
ause of this, it becomes a great tool to learn Sudoku solving techniques th=
rough numerous examples.</p><p>To use our Sudoku solver, just enter your va=
lid Sudoku puzzle in the blank grid above.  If you want a step by step solu=
tion with an explanation for each step, press the "Step by Step Solution" b=
utton, and it will bring up our smart Sudoku solver to give you the solutio=
n with step by step explanations. If you just want a solution for your puzz=
le, press the "Solution Only" button, and it will give you the solution ins=
tantly.</p><p>You may also use our Sudoku solver to check whether your Sudo=
ku puzzle is valid or not. If your puzzle is not valid (having no solution =
or more than one solution), you will get an alert from our Sudoku solver wh=
en pressing the "Solution Only" button or the "Step by Step Solution" butto=
n.</p></div>
